Notes for Xitrum developers.

Netty 4
-------

**This part will be removed when Netty 4 is officially released.**

File upload feature in Xitrum needs `Netty <https://github.com/netty/netty>`_ 4,
which has not been released. You must build it yourself.

::

  git clone https://github.com/netty/netty.git

Add to its pom.xml:

::

  <repositories>
     <repository>
       <id>repository.jboss.org</id>
       <name>JBoss Releases Repository</name>
       <url>http://repository.jboss.org/maven2</url>
     </repository>
   </repositories>

   <pluginRepositories>
     <pluginRepository>
       <id>repository.jboss.org</id>
       <name>JBoss Releases Repository</name>
       <url>http://repository.jboss.org/maven2</url>
     </pluginRepository>
   </pluginRepositories>

Build with `Maven <http://maven.apache.org/>`_:

::

  $ wget http://bit.ly/jebzNn
  $ mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=org.jboss.logging -DartifactId=jboss-logging-spi \
    -Dpackaging=jar -Dversion=2.1.2.GA -Dfile=jboss-logging-spi-2.1.2.GA.jar -DgeneratePom=true
  $ MAVEN_OPTS=-Xmx512m mvn -Dmaven.test.skip=true install

Above is the quick and dirty way. Long way: https://issues.jboss.org/browse/NETTY-387.

Delete snapshots
----------------

While developing, you may need to publish and delete published snapshots.

To publish, run ``sbt`` then from SBT command prompt run ``+ publish``.

To delete snapshots:

::

  rm .ivy2//cache/tv.cntt/xitrum-plugin_2.8.1/jars/xitrum-plugin_2.8.1-1.1-SNAPSHOT.jar

